object.field:
Concatenates the value of the channel with the value of the string given by the user.
e.g. Channel value: 'aaa' String (given by user): 'bbb' Returns: 'aaabbb'

Encodes the value of the channel as a valid component of a universal resource identifier (URI, Uniform Resource Identifier).
e.g. Channel value: 'ezweb platform' Returns: 'ezweb%20platform'

Takes the value of the channel as a universal resource identifier (URI, Uniform Resource Identifier) and returns its string version decoded.
e.g. Channel value: 'ezweb%20platform' Returns: 'ezweb platform'

Searchs for a specified value in the value of the channel using regular expressions.
e.g. Search in the beginning of the value for capital letters Channel value: 'EzWeb' Regular expresion (given by user): '^[A-Z]*' Returns: 'E'

Searchs for a specified value in the value of the channel using regular expressions, and replaces it with the string given by the user.
e.g. Replaces the brackets with a empty character (removes the bracket) Channel value: '(304)4345454' Regular expresion (given by user): '/[\(\)]/g' Returns: '3044345454'

Divides the value of the channel into substrings using the delimiter given, and creates an array containing the resulting substrings. The delimiter value is not returned as part of the array of substrings.
e.g. Channel value: 'Internet' Delimiter (given by user): 'e' Returns: 'Int, rn, t'

Extracts a specified number of characters from a string beginning at the specified start index.
e.g. Channel value: 'EzWeb' Start index (given by user): '2' Length (given by user): '3' Returns: 'Web'

Downcases all the letters of the value of the channel.
e.g. Channel value: 'EZWEB' Returns: 'ezweb'

Capitalizes all the letters of the value of the channel.
e.g. Channel value: 'ezweb' Returns: 'EZWEB'
